---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Recruitment System" description="How troop recruitment works in TAOM - the four-tier structure">
  <div class="page-content mod-info">
    <nav class="breadcrumb">
      <a href="/mod-info">&larr; Mod Info</a>
    </nav>

    <h1 class="page-title">Recruitment System Overview</h1>
    <p class="page-subtitle">A New Four-Tier Structure</p>

    <section class="intro-section">
      <p>
        To better reflect regional diversity and faction identity, <em>Tales from the Age of Men</em> introduces a
        <strong>new four-tier recruitment structure</strong> that applies to <strong>every faction</strong> in the mod.
        Troops no longer fall into just "standard" and "noble" categories; instead, armies are formed through a
        layered system of <span class="tier-tag regular">Regular</span>, <span class="tier-tag noble">Noble</span>,
        <span class="tier-tag regional">Regional</span>, and <span class="tier-tag unique">Unique</span> units,
        each with its own availability and rarity.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="tier-cards">
      <div class="tier-card">
        <div class="tier-card-header regular">
          <h2>Regular Units</h2>
          <span class="tier-pct">40-50%</span>
        </div>
        <p>
          Form the foundation of every army. These are the most common troops and can be recruited consistently
          across <strong>all settlements</strong> within their faction's territory.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="tier-card">
        <div class="tier-card-header noble">
          <h2>Noble Units</h2>
          <span class="tier-pct">10-20%</span>
        </div>
        <p>
          Follow the classic Bannerlord rule: they remain <strong>globally recruitable</strong> within their faction's
          lands, but appear in <strong>small numbers</strong> and represent elite households, officer retinues, or
          aristocratic warriors.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="tier-card">
        <div class="tier-card-header regional">
          <h2>Regional Units</h2>
          <span class="tier-pct">30-40%</span>
        </div>
        <p>
          Tied to <strong>specific homelands</strong> &mdash; certain cities, castles, or villages based on their
          cultural or geographic origins. They are <strong>more specialized</strong> and <strong>rarer</strong>,
          making up a significant but location-dependent portion of a settlement's recruits.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="tier-card">
        <div class="tier-card-header unique">
          <h2>Unique Units</h2>
          <span class="tier-pct">Rare</span>
        </div>
        <p>
          Tied to <strong>only one or two settlements</strong> in the entire game. These represent exceptional
          formations, sacred orders, or legendary warriors. While not every faction currently fields one,
          future updates will expand this category.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="gameplay-section">
      <h2>In Practice</h2>
      <p>
        A typical garrison or settlement recruit pool might appear as roughly
        <strong class="regular-text">40-50% Regular</strong> troops,
        <strong class="noble-text">10-20% Noble</strong> troops, and
        <strong class="regional-text">30-40% Regional</strong> troops,
        with <strong class="unique-text">Unique</strong> units being extremely limited and tied to specific
        strategic locations.
      </p>
      <p>
        This structure creates deeper faction identity and encourages players to expand into &mdash; or defend &mdash;
        key regions to unlock their full military potential.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="bar-chart-section">
      <h3>Typical Settlement Recruit Composition</h3>
      <div class="bar-chart">
        <div class="bar-segment regular" style="flex: 45">
          <span>Regular</span>
          <span>~45%</span>
        </div>
        <div class="bar-segment noble" style="flex: 15">
          <span>Noble</span>
          <span>~15%</span>
        </div>
        <div class="bar-segment regional" style="flex: 35">
          <span>Regional</span>
          <span>~35%</span>
        </div>
        <div class="bar-segment unique" style="flex: 5">
          <span>Unique</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .mod-info {
    max-width: 900px;
  }

  .breadcrumb {
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .breadcrumb a {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
  }

  .breadcrumb a:hover {
    color: var(--accent);
  }

  .page-subtitle {
    color: var(--accent);
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    margin-top: -0.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .intro-section {
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    font-size: 1rem;
  }

  .tier-tag {
    font-weight: 700;
    padding: 0.1rem 0.4rem;
    border-radius: 3px;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
  }

  .tier-tag.regular { color: #4CAF50; }
  .tier-tag.noble { color: #AB47BC; }
  .tier-tag.regional { color: #42A5F5; }
  .tier-tag.unique { color: #FFA726; }

  .tier-cards {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(380px, 1fr));
    gap: 1.25rem;
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
  }

  .tier-card {
    background: var(--bg-secondary);
    border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
    border-radius: 8px;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .tier-card-header {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: center;
    padding: 0.75rem 1.25rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-color);
  }

  .tier-card-header h2 {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .tier-pct {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    opacity: 0.8;
  }

  .tier-card-header.regular { border-left: 4px solid #4CAF50; }
  .tier-card-header.regular h2 { color: #4CAF50; }
  .tier-card-header.regular .tier-pct { color: #4CAF50; }

  .tier-card-header.noble { border-left: 4px solid #AB47BC; }
  .tier-card-header.noble h2 { color: #AB47BC; }
  .tier-card-header.noble .tier-pct { color: #AB47BC; }

  .tier-card-header.regional { border-left: 4px solid #42A5F5; }
  .tier-card-header.regional h2 { color: #42A5F5; }
  .tier-card-header.regional .tier-pct { color: #42A5F5; }

  .tier-card-header.unique { border-left: 4px solid #FFA726; }
  .tier-card-header.unique h2 { color: #FFA726; }
  .tier-card-header.unique .tier-pct { color: #FFA726; }

  .tier-card p {
    padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .gameplay-section {
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
  }

  .gameplay-section h2 {
    color: var(--accent);
    font-size: 1.3rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-color);
  }

  .gameplay-section p {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .regular-text { color: #4CAF50; }
  .noble-text { color: #AB47BC; }
  .regional-text { color: #42A5F5; }
  .unique-text { color: #FFA726; }

  .bar-chart-section {
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .bar-chart-section h3 {
    color: var(--text-primary);
    font-size: 1rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .bar-chart {
    display: flex;
    border-radius: 6px;
    overflow: hidden;
    height: 48px;
  }

  .bar-segment {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #fff;
    gap: 0.1rem;
  }

  .bar-segment.regular { background: #4CAF50; }
  .bar-segment.noble { background: #AB47BC; }
  .bar-segment.regional { background: #42A5F5; }
  .bar-segment.unique { background: #FFA726; }

  @media (max-width: 600px) {
    .tier-cards {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
